Small groups analyzed which recruiters appeared most enthusiastic, while volunteers stacked collapsed booths and collected leftover brochures amidst the aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafting from the lounge. Monitors displayed a post-event survey link, and a whiteboard showcased employers scheduling same-day interviews. The dean expressed gratitude to the recruiters, and announcement chimes signaled the final hour of the fair. Additionally, tech companies demonstrated their latest apps, and a cybersecurity company hosted a password cracking challenge. Friends relaxed on the quad, comparing experiences, while international students sought advice on visa sponsorship requirements.

Human resources teams jot notes on tablets, while students utilize kiosks to upload resumes, fill out interview sign-up sheets, and analyze recruiter enthusiasm. The engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, complemented by an alumni panel discussing tips for technical interviews. Small groups discuss enthusiastic recruiters, friends decompress on the quad, and as the fair concludes, volunteers collect leftover materials while many exit with tote bags filled with notebooks, pens, water bottles, and business cards.

At the event's conclusion, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover materials, with many students departing with stacks of business cards, comparing contents, and marking target employers on event maps.
